        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:44PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Calawassie Island, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beaufort, Port Royal, Clarendon, Jasper, Lemon Island, Shell
Point, Burton, Laurel Bay, Calawassie Island and Beaufort Marine
Corps Air Station.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
